{"name": "unpackable", "metadata": {"name": "unpackable", "version": "0.0.4", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "", "license": "LGPL-3.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "\ud83d\udce6 Destructure Python objects", "upload_time": 1630795641}, "documentation": ["# Unpackable: Object destructuring for Python\n`unpackable` is a module that lets you use [Python's destructuring assignment](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-3132/) to unpack an object's attributes.\n\n## Use case\nConsider [JavaScript's destructuring assignment](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Destructuring_assignment) feature that allows you to do the following:\n```javascript\nclass User {\n  constructor(id, email) {\n    this.id = id;\n    this.email = email;\n  }\n}\n\nconst user = new User(1, 'example@example.com')\nconst {id, email} = user;  // destructure\n```\n\n`unpackable` allows you to do something similar in Python:\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom unpackable import Unpackable\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass User(Unpackable):\n  id: int\n  email: str\n\n\nuser = User(1, 'example@example.com')\nid, email = user  # destructure\n```\n\n`unpackable` can also unpack objects that don't subclass `Unpackable`:\n```python\nfrom unpackable import unpack\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass User:\n  id: int\n  email: str\n\n\nuser = User(1, 'example@example.com')\nid, email = unpack(user)  # destructure\n```\n\n# Status\n`unpackable` currently works with iterable objects, `dataclasses` and simple objects.\n\nThis is alpha software and is not ready for use beyond limited use cases like in [my `app_paths` project](https://github.com/alexdelorenzo/app_paths).\n\n# Installation\n## Requirements\n - Python 3.8+\n\n## PyPI\n```bash\npython3 -m pip install unpackable\n```\n\n# Support\nWant to support this project and [other open-source projects](https://github.com/alexdelorenzo) like it?\n\n<a href=\"https://www.buymeacoffee.com/alexdelorenzo\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://cdn.buymeacoffee.com/buttons/v2/default-yellow.png\" alt=\"Buy Me A Coffee\" height=\"60px\" style=\"height: 60px !important;width: 217px !important;max-width:25%\" ></a>\n\n# License\nSee `LICENSE`. If you'd like to use this project with a different license, please get in touch.\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "unpackable.obj", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "unpackable.obj.sort_by_name", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "key_val", "type": {"name": "KeyVal", "xref": {"fqname": "KeyVal", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Key", "xref": {"fqname": "Key", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "unpackable.obj.sort_by_val", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "key_val", "type": {"name": "KeyVal", "xref": {"fqname": "KeyVal", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Val", "xref": {"fqname": "Val", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "unpackable.obj.gen_keys", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Key", "xref": {"fqname": "Key", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Return all members of an obj as (name, value) pairs sorted by name.\nOptionally, only return members that satisfy a given predicate."]}, {"name": "unpackable.obj.gen_results", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "predicate", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname"